cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

The paper deals with automatic facial action unit recognition, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel end-to-end trainable framework, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of 3D face models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper's focus on facial expressions and emotions could also place it under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
